{"id":"283755481_A_demonstration_of_adaptive_weather_surveillance_and_multifunction_capabilities_on_the_National_Weather_Radar_Testbed_Phased_Array_Radar","abstract":"This paper describes the latest adaptive scanning and multifunction capabilities of the National Weather Radar Testbed Phased-Array Radar located in Norman, Oklahoma (USA). Proof-of-concept focused and tailored observations of weather and scheduling algorithms for multifunction operation are described, and their performance is illustrated with real-data examples. It is demonstrated that adaptive scanning of weather is feasible in a multifunction radar and has the potential to reduce revisit times and to provide meteorological data that can aid in the forecaster's warning-decision process.","authors":["Sebastian M. Torres","Richard Adams","Christopher Curtis","Eddie Forren"],"meta":["March 2015Proceedings of the IEEE 104(3)","DOI:10.1109/RADAR.2014.7060420"],"references":["322640389_Multifunction_Phased-Array_Radar_Time_Balance_Scheduler_for_Adaptive_Weather_Sensing","273489758_Tornado_Warning_Decisions_Using_Phased-Array_Radar_Data","273344642_Impacts_of_Phased_Array_Radar_Data_on_Forecaster_Performance_during_Severe_Hail_and_Wind_Events","272429087_Scanning_Strategy_for_the_Multifunction_Phased-Array_Radar_to_Satisfy_Aviation_and_Meteorological_Needs","267154915_Radial-Based_Noise_Power_Estimation_for_Weather_Radars","265675590_6B3_ADAPTS_IMPLEMENTATION_CAN_WE_EXPLOIT_PHASED-ARRAY_RADAR'S_ELECTRONIC_BEAM_STEERING_CAPABILITIES_TO_REDUCE_UPDATE_TIMES","260461118_The_Use_of_Coherency_to_Improve_Signal_Detection_in_Dual-Polarization_Weather_Radars","260347749_7_AN_ADAPTIVE_PEDESTAL_CONTROL_ALGORITHM_FOR_THE_NATIONAL_WEATHER_RADAR_TESTBED_PHASED_ARRAY_RADAR","249616047_Agile-Beam_Phased_Array_Radar_for_Weather_Observations","241397733_The_Next-Generation_Multimission_US_Surveillance_Radar_Network","228931343_High-Temporal_Resolution_Capabilities_of_the_National_Weather_Radar_Testbed_Phased-Array_Radar","22